231. Power of Two

Given an integer n, return true if it is a power of two. Otherwise, return false.

An integer n is a power of two, if there exists an integer x such that n == 2x.
Example 1:

Input: n = 1
Output: true
Explanation: 20 = 1
Example 2:

class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfTwo(int n) {
        if(n==1) return true;
        if( n==0) return false;
        while( n!=1)
        {
            if( n%2!=0)
            {
                return false;
            }
            n=n/2;
        }
        return true;
    }
}


int power = 1;

while (power <= n) {
    if (power == n) {
        return true;
    }
    power = power * 2;
}

